(427, ' Prepare beef pot pie and mashed potatoes as directed on packages. In ovenproof dish layer beef pot pie , then mashed potatoes; top with cheese. Place in oven or microwave until cheese is melted. Eat and enjoy.', '1 beef pot pie', '2 servings instant mashed potatoes', '1 slice American cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(428, ' Drain the spinach in a sieve; do not press out water. Combine the spinach , soup mix , sour cream and bread crumbs; mix well. Blend in the eggs. Pour into a greased 2 1/2-quart casserole. Top with cheese. Bake at 350&deg; for 45 minutes. Makes 10 to 12 servings.', '4 (10 oz.) pkg. frozen , chopped spinach , thawed', '1 (2 3/4 oz.) box dry onion soup mix', '1 pt. sour cream', '1 c. seasoned bread crumbs', '4 eggs , beaten', ' Swiss cheese , shredded', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(430, ' Mix all ingredients in a bowl. Form into 3 to 4 balls. Put oil in a frying pan. Cook meat balls until light brown all over and no longer pink inside (15 minutes).', '2 1/2 Tbsp. ground beef', '1 1/2 Tbsp. milk', '1 Tbsp. bread crumbs', '1 tsp. Parmesan cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(433, ' Slice bread lengthwise , then into strips and finally into cubes about 1 to 2-inches square. Place on cookie sheet and heat in a 425&deg; oven until tan. Remove and put in a bread basket. Put sauce in baking dish and heat in microwave until hot. Remove and sprinkle cheese on top. When cheese melts , put on table with bread. Give each child a fork and let him or her stab a cube of bread and dip it into sauce. No mess and no waste,', '1 loaf Italian bread , unsliced', '1 c. Mozzarella cheese , shredded', '1 large or 2 small jars pizza sauce', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(438, ' Split , skin and bone chicken; arrange in shallow baking pan. Top each with a piece of cheese. Stir soup and water together and spoon on top of chicken. Sprinkle with stuffing and drizzle with butter. Bake , uncovered , at 350&deg; for 50 minutes.', '3 whole chicken breasts', '6 (1 oz.) slices Swiss cheese', '1 can cream of chicken soup', '1/4 c. water', '1 box Stove Top stuffing', '1/3 c. melted butter', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(440, ' Prepare vegetables. In medium saucepan , melt margarine; add vegetables and saut&eacute; until slightly soft (5 to 10 minutes). Meanwhile , cut hot dogs into 1/4-inch pennies. Add meat , soup and milk to pan with vegetables. Heat about 10 minutes. Add cheese; let rest a few minutes to soften and partially melt cheese. Serve with crisp crackers.', '2 c. total combined in any desired portions: thinly sliced carrots , celery , green pepper and onion', '1 to 2 Tbsp. margarine', '2 to 3 hot dogs', '1 can condensed cream soup (chicken , etc.)', '1 can milk', ' pepper (if desired)', '1/4 to 1/2 c. of Cheddar cheese chunks', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(442, ' Combine first 7 ingredients. Mix lightly. Split buns and fill. Heat wrapped in foil in slow 250&deg; oven for about 30 minutes or until filling is bubbly and cheese is melted. Great with chips and hot chocolate.', '1/4 lb. American cheese (1 c. cubed)', '3 hard boiled eggs , chopped', '1 (7 oz.) tuna , flaked', '2 Tbsp. chopped onion', '2 Tbsp. chopped olives', '2 Tbsp. chopped sweet pickles', '1/2 c. mayonnaise or salad dressing', '6 wiener buns', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(444, ' Have children flatten biscuits. Then have them place meat and cheese on each biscuit and wrap biscuit around the meat and cheese , sealing all edges. Place on greased cookie sheet and brush each dipper with melted butter or margarine. Bake at 400&deg; for 10 to 12 minutes or until nicely browned. Serve with a dipping sauce of your choice. Serves 4.', '1 pkg. refrigerator biscuits', '2 x 2 x 1/2-inch cooked meat pieces (chicken , pork , beef or ham)', '2 x 2 x 1/2-inch cheese pieces (Swiss or Mozzarella)', ' honey or jalapeno jelly (optional)', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(447, ' Fix your favorite tuna salad or simply mix 1 can of tuna with Miracle Whip salad dressing. Pop one piece of bread into toaster. Spread the tuna on top. Place a slice of cheese on the top and stick it on a cookie sheet. Turn the oven on broil and put it under the broiler for a couple of minutes until the cheese melts.', '1 can tuna', ' Miracle Whip salad dressing', ' bread', ' cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(453, ' Wash hands, Brown beef , drain grease. This is done with adult help. Mix spaghetti sauce into ground beef. Beat eggs. Add cottage cheese , Parmesan cheese and 1 cup shredded cheese to eggs. Add oregano or Italian seasoning. Mix well. Place 3 uncooked lasagna noodles in a 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish. Measure 1 1/3 cups meat mixture and spread over noodles. Spread 1/2 of egg-cheese mixture over meat mixture. Repeat noodles , meat , then egg-cheese mixture. Top with 3 more uncooked noodles and remaining meat mixture. Pour the hot water around all 4 edges of dish. Cover with foil. Bake at 350&deg; for 1 1/4 hours. Sprinkle remaining Mozzarella cheese on top and cool 10 minutes before serving.', '1 lb. ground beef', '1 (15 1/2 oz.) jar spaghetti sauce', '2 eggs', '1 1/2 c. cottage cheese', '1/4 c. Parmesan cheese', '6 oz. (1 1/2 c.) shredded Mozzarella cheese', '1 tsp. oregano or Italian seasoning', '9 lasagna noodles', '3/4 c. hot water', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(455, ' Cook spaghetti according to directions. Put in 9 x 13-inch pan , add unheated soups and rinse cans with milk; add milk , tuna and half the potato chips. Mix well. Sprinkle remaining chips on top to cover. Bake at 325&deg; until warm. Serve with salad or favorite vegetable.', '16 oz. pkg. spaghetti', '1 (10 3/4 oz.) can cream of mushroom soup', '1 (10 3/4 oz.) can cream of chicken soup', '1 soup can milk', '1 (8 oz.) can tuna', '2 c. plain crushed potato chips', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(456, ' Brown hamburger until it is no longer pink. Add cut up vegetables , peas , seasonings , soup and water. Bake in 350&deg; oven or on top of stove until vegetables are tender. Stir as needed.', '1 lb. hamburger', '2 carrots', '1 medium onion', '2 potatoes', '2 stalks celery', '1 (10 oz.) pkg. frozen peas , thawed', ' salt and pepper', '1 can tomato soup', '1/2 can water', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(457, ' Combine all ingredients , adding 1/2 of onion rings last. Mix well. Place in greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350&deg; for about 30 to 40 minutes or until mixture bubbles. Sprinkle remaining onion rings over top last 5 minutes. Remove; let sit 5 minutes before serving. This is good to make ahead and refrigerate until ready to use. Baking time will be longer if refrigerated.', '1 lb. lean ground beef , browned', '1 lb. frozen shredded hash brown potatoes , completely thawed', '1 c. sour cream', '1 c. grated Cheddar cheese', '1 can undiluted mushroom soup', '1/2 tsp. salt', '1 can French fried onions , divided', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(461, ' Mix all ingredients and bake in a buttered 1-quart casserole at 350&deg; for 25 minutes. Serves 6.', '1 lb. wieners , chopped', '1 small can evaporated milk', '1 can cream of chicken soup', '1 can cream of celery soup', '1 (5 oz.) can Chinese noodles', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(462, ' Cook meat and onion until brown; drain fat. Remove from heat. Stir in the sauce , olives , basil and oregano. Cut a thin slice from top of each roll. Hollow out bottom of roll to within 1/2-inch of edges. Sprinkle about 3 tablespoons cheese into each roll bottom. Spoon meat mixture over each. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Replace roll tops. Wrap individually in foil and refrigerate or freeze.', '1 lb. ground beef', '1/2 c. chopped onion', '16 oz. pizza sauce', '4 Tbsp. chopped black olives', '2 tsp. dried crushed basil', '1 tsp. dried crushed oregano', '6 French rolls (about 8-inches long)', '12 oz. shredded Mozzarella cheese', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(463, ' Brown bacon. Add next 10 ingredients. Cover and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes. Add green beans , peas and spaghetti and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.', '1 lb. bacon , cut in 1/4-inch pieces', '2 Tbsp. tomato puree or leftover sauce', '2 cloves garlic', ' pepper to taste', '3 to 4 c. peeled , chopped potatoes', '1 onion , chopped', '1 c. chopped carrots', '1 c. chopped celery', '2 to 3 qt. chicken stock or water and bouillon', '1 Tbsp. parsley', '1 Tbsp. basil', '1 (10 oz.) pkg. frozen green beans', '1 (10 oz.) pkg. frozen peas', '4 oz. broken spaghetti', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(464, ' Place all ingredients in separate bowls and have the children create their own pizzas. Place on cookie sheet and bake at 400&deg; until cheese is melted. Great idea for sleepovers and birthday parties.', '1 pkg. pita bread (10 to 12)', '2 lb. Mozzarella cheese , shredded', '1 onion , diced', '1 medium green pepper , diced', '1 pkg. pepperoni , sliced', '1/2 to 1 lb. sausage , cooked', '1/2 lb. mushrooms , sliced', '2 cans pizza sauce', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
